# git archive export-subst: when ``git archive`` creates a release tarball or
# zip, git substitutes $Format:…$ placeholders in the listed file with the
# actual commit metadata.  This allows the package to report its exact git
# version even when installed from a tarball where the .git directory is absent.
#
# Usage:
#   git archive HEAD --format=tar.gz -o mutation_scatter_plot-HEAD.tar.gz
#   (then inspect _version.py inside the archive – the hashes will be expanded)
#
# See also: gitattributes(5), "Performing conversion upon archive"
src/mutation_scatter_plot/mutation_scatter_plot/_version.py export-subst
